  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The COU narrative requires that the model be validated only for tip-speed regimes below 4 m/s to bound erythrocyte damage exposure; this upper tip-speed constraint is a critical safety property for Class II CPB devices and is explicitly referenced in the intended-use description as a prerequisite for the hemolysis acceptance criterion RH < 1. However, the bound requirement record linked from this package addresses only flow-rate and pressure-head tolerances and does not enumerate the tip-speed upper bound as a named obligation, leaving that safety property unstated in the structured requirement set.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-req-flow-pressure-only",
